    Decoder = student who writes an answer based on what was read.

The decoder keeps asking:

    “Given what I’ve written so far… what should I write next?”

It never sees the future. Only the past.

That’s why it uses masked self-attention.
🔒 Why Masking?

Because when generating:

If we are predicting word #5, we cannot look at word #6.

So we block future tokens using a causal mask.

That’s the key difference from encoder attention.
🔄 What Happens Inside the Decoder?

Each decoder block has:

    ✅ Masked self-attention (looks only backward)
